-[GROANS]

308
00:11:28,866 --> 00:11:30,200
[IMOGENE SIGHS]

309
00:11:30,284 --> 00:11:32,494
So, we should finalize the guest list.

310
00:11:32,578 --> 00:11:34,621
-It's the same as last year.
-Is it?

311
00:11:34,705 --> 00:11:36,623
What's the confusion, Dody?

312
00:11:36,707 --> 00:11:37,791
Is Joel coming?

313
00:11:37,875 --> 00:11:39,000
Of course he's coming

314
00:11:39,084 --> 00:11:40,418
it's his son's birthday.

315
00:11:40,502 --> 00:11:41,962
Is he bringing her?

316
00:11:42,046 --> 00:11:44,047
Only if he wants to be beaten to death

317
00:11:44,131 --> 00:11:45,966
by, I don't know, everyone at the party.

318
00:11:46,050 --> 00:11:48,759
Okay. But we'd better figure out
who knows what, compare stories.

319
00:11:48,843 --> 00:11:49,092
Stories?

320
00:11:49,176 --> 00:11:50,803
The stories you've
each been telling people

321
00:11:50,887 --> 00:11:52,763
about your situation…
I've completely lost track.

322
00:11:52,847 --> 00:11:55,766
And I have no idea what
you've been telling people.

323
00:11:55,850 --> 00:11:58,811
Every word, as if broadcast
over a microphone.

324
00:11:58,895 --> 00:12:01,689
-We're almost done.
-You keep starting over.

325
00:12:01,773 --> 00:12:03,065
She talked me out of
gender-specific bags,

326
00:12:03,149 --> 00:12:05,401
-Mr. Weissman.
-[EXHALES]

327
00:12:05,485 --> 00:12:08,362
Set up a line like Henry Ford.

328
00:12:08,446 --> 00:12:10,030
Keep the piles separate,

329
00:12:10,114 --> 00:12:12,116
then pass the bags from one to the other.

330
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:14,076
Candy cigarettes, pass the bag,

331
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:16,036
a Silly Putty, pass the bag, and so on.

332
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:18,122
Thanks for the industrial
education, Papa.

333
00:12:18,206 --> 00:12:20,123
And, young lady, I heard through the door

334
00:12:20,207 --> 00:12:22,333
that your name is not Dody…
what is your name?

335
00:12:22,417 --> 00:12:23,626
Imogene.

336
00:12:23,710 --> 00:12:26,129
I'm not gonna remember that.

337
00:12:27,964 --> 00:12:30,883
The Murphys… do they know all?

338
00:12:30,967 --> 00:12:33,886
I'm not sure.
I… I lied to some people at first,

339
00:12:33,970 --> 00:12:35,722
then started telling people
that we were separated

340
00:12:35,806 --> 00:12:38,141
-but trying to work it out.
-The Turners?

341
00:12:38,225 --> 00:12:40,893
Think that Joel is on a
business trip in Poland.

342
00:12:40,977 --> 00:12:43,187
-The Rivingtons?
-Know that you're separated

343
00:12:43,271 --> 00:12:45,273
and know that Joel moved out.
Someone got to them before me.

344
00:12:45,357 --> 00:12:47,275
But they don't know that
Joel's living with Penny.

345
00:12:47,359 --> 00:12:49,360
He's not living with Penny anymore.

346
00:12:49,444 --> 00:12:50,485
What? Since when?

347
00:12:50,569 --> 00:12:51,695
Joel's secretary called.

348
00:12:51,779 --> 00:12:53,113
Gave me a new home number for him.

349
00:12:53,197 --> 00:12:54,615
It was his parents'.

350
00:12:54,699 --> 00:12:55,616
What happened?

351
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:56,867
I don't know.

352
00:12:56,951 --> 00:12:58,285
Wow.

353
00:12:58,369 --> 00:12:59,870
As the world turns.

354
00:12:59,954 --> 00:13:03,915
-Mm-hmm.
-So, who else? Uh, the Gertzs.

355
00:13:03,999 --> 00:13:06,752
MIDGE: Think that Joel is
on a very long business trip

356
00:13:06,836 --> 00:13:09,087
-but suspect more.
-The Salings?

357
00:13:09,171 --> 00:13:11,006
MIDGE: Think that we are
renovating the apartment

358
00:13:11,090 --> 00:13:13,342
and that Joel is traveling for work.

359
00:13:13,426 --> 00:13:16,076
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]
-[COMMENTATOR SPEAKING ON RADIO]

360
00:13:21,016 --> 00:13:22,684
Mm.

361
00:13:27,021 --> 00:13:28,272
What the hell?

362
00:13:28,356 --> 00:13:29,940
Harry, good. Can we talk?

363
00:13:30,024 --> 00:13:31,359
Oh, Susie. Sure.

364
00:13:31,443 --> 00:13:33,194
Hey, uh, guys, can you give us the room?

365
00:13:33,278 --> 00:13:35,029
-Susie needs to talk to me.
-[CHUCKLING]

366
00:13:35,113 --> 00:13:36,489
You don't have to clear the room.

367
00:13:36,573 --> 00:13:38,157
I'm not gonna clear the goddamn room.

368
00:13:38,241 --> 00:13:39,825
Jesus Christ, Susie, get a phone.

369
00:13:39,909 --> 00:13:42,411
-I have a phone.
-Well, use it.

370
00:13:42,495 --> 00:13:44,330
