when I'm on the telephone

433
00:15:40,651 --> 00:15:43,111
and I say my name, Sophie Lennon,

434
00:15:43,195 --> 00:15:45,906
people think they hear "Sophia Loren."
Mm.

435
00:15:45,990 --> 00:15:46,865
[AWWING]

436
00:15:46,949 --> 00:15:49,701
Funny, nobody ever makes
that mistake in person.

437
00:15:49,785 --> 00:15:50,952
[LAUGHTER]

438
00:15:51,036 --> 00:15:53,371
You hear those laughs?

439
00:15:53,455 --> 00:15:54,956
They're big laughs.

440
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:56,875
Are you sure my stuff is
funny enough for Harry?

441
00:15:56,959 --> 00:15:59,210
Positive. Why? Aren't you sure?

442
00:15:59,294 --> 00:16:01,462
-I'm pretty sure.
-Pretty sure?

443
00:16:01,546 --> 00:16:04,548
I went out on a limb for you
here, sister, so be damn sure.

444
00:16:04,632 --> 00:16:06,550
I'm… damn sure, okay?

445
00:16:06,634 --> 00:16:09,220
I mean, really.

446
00:16:09,304 --> 00:16:11,388
Yeah, I like to eat!

447
00:16:11,472 --> 00:16:15,976
-I'm so fat…
-ALL: How fat are you?

448
00:16:16,060 --> 00:16:19,313
I'm so fat that I used
to look Rubenesque,

449
00:16:19,397 --> 00:16:22,691
and now I just look
like a Reuben sandwich.

450
00:16:22,775 --> 00:16:24,693
[LAUGHTER]

451
00:16:24,777 --> 00:16:27,696
I grew up listening to
this woman on the radio.

452
00:16:27,780 --> 00:16:30,031
-Me, too.
-Even my dad laughed at her.

453
00:16:30,115 --> 00:16:31,616
He tried not to, but he did.

454
00:16:31,700 --> 00:16:34,285
She got a lot of us
through the Depression.

455
00:16:34,369 --> 00:16:35,954
How old are you?

456
00:16:36,038 --> 00:16:38,122
I'm not telling you.

457
00:16:38,206 --> 00:16:39,958
I can't even go to the beach anymore.

458
00:16:40,042 --> 00:16:41,793
Last time I was at the beach,

459
00:16:41,877 --> 00:16:44,879
